text:
20/11/2024
Visited this mall to get some snacks. Cosy small mall with F&B outlets, supermarket, clinic & school. Limited chargeable gantry open-air parking available.
This mall has nothing much going on. There are, however, a supermarket (Cold Storage), three cafes, an ice cream parlour and a cake shop.
Male toilet is poorly maintained.  One of the three taps have not been in working conditions for more than ten weeks. One of the toilet cubicles is taped on the door for sometimes.
There is a bakery, ice cream parlour, Cold Storage, childhood education and some other niche shops. Cosy area.

Nice cozy place with the essentials of a good day, except that the security guard is quite mean ... Context, I tripped a bit when I tried to open the back door and he just straight up scolded me for rushing (?). Really ruined my morning, right after I just got nice pastries from Baker and Cook.

No one to complain usually on reviews but was truly disappointed by this experience, such a lovely place but rude guard.
